Reported through our Ecosystem Developer Servicedesk:

REST API: rest/api/latest/result for a specific build that has associated (non-public) JIRA issues and using *expand=jiraIssues*.

It appears this API will fail trying to access a application link:
{noformat}
{"status-code":401,"authenticationInstanceName":"JIRA","message":"Client must be authenticated to access this resource.","authenticationRedirectUrl":"https:\/\/builddev.appfire.com\/plugins\/servlet\/applinks\/oauth\/login-dance\/authorize?applicationLinkID=b98585c5-0090-3dc5-9aab-8d6d8d023ee2"}
{noformat}
Not exactly sure why it things the app link is broken, but, I think the bigger issue here is why would a results requests fail for this indirect authentication problem? Specifically, it already knows the JIRA keys without contacting the anyone. Not to mention the performance impact that is undesirable. At least in my case, I just need the keys and I would expect that if more details are required that involved an expensive operation that that would need to be requested specifically.

Furthermore, if one did want more information that required access to the remote resource like this, how would that authentication information be passed in if the app link configuration required that.

